1065
00:59:08,320 --> 00:59:09,719
whether the Crown Prince is the one who tried to kill you.

1066
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:12,159
Don't act rashly on your own.

1067
00:59:13,159 --> 00:59:14,199
Act rashly?

1068
00:59:15,159 --> 00:59:16,159
What can I do?

1069
00:59:17,039 --> 00:59:18,880
Can I rush into the Eastern Palace and kill the Crown Prince?

1070
00:59:21,679 --> 00:59:22,800
Back then,

1071
00:59:24,199 --> 00:59:26,280
your mom could really do that!

1072
00:59:27,599 --> 00:59:28,199
So awesome!

1073
00:59:28,960 --> 00:59:31,239
She was bound to no rules of the world.

1074
00:59:32,599 --> 00:59:34,039
She could always

1075
00:59:34,840 --> 00:59:36,360
make unexpected moves.

1076
00:59:39,719 --> 00:59:40,559
How did she die?

1077
00:59:42,880 --> 00:59:43,840
She was killed.

1078
00:59:45,000 --> 00:59:46,119
Those who killed her, are they still alive?

1079
00:59:46,400 --> 00:59:47,199
I've no idea.

1080
00:59:47,880 --> 00:59:48,760
In theory,

1081
00:59:49,599 --> 00:59:51,719
